From 21aed75e850bde986e21f0088bc9e217488a8361 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 7 Mar 2026 04:25:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix lower-priority issues found in deep codebase audit
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

attention.py:
- Fix post-softmax clamping leaking through causal mask: use torch.where
  to only clamp non-masked positions, keeping masked positions at exact 0
- Guard against division by zero in attention re-normalization

variational_ffn.py:
- Fix in-place += breaking autograd in block-diagonal sigma gradient
- Add epsilon guard to all kappa_scaled divisions (6 locations)
- Add epsilon clamp before torch.log in diagonal KL computations (3 locations)
- Remove dead else branches in tuple unpacking (return_kl always returns tuple)
- Add clarifying comment about chunked VFE memory accumulators

pure_fep_transformer.py:
- Fix division by zero: use max(N, 1) in prior alignment gradient
- Fix in-place clamp_ on prior_sigma buffer: use .data.clamp_()
- Fix dead code in decode path: add explicit None check for prior_bank

fep_transformer.py:
- Fix rodrigues_so3 catastrophic cancellation for small angles: use Taylor
  expansion (sin(θ)/θ ≈ 1-θ²/6, (1-cos θ)/θ² ≈ 1/2-θ²/24) when θ < 1e-4
- Fix diagonal covariance transport: apply Ω²σ instead of identity (was
  assuming isotropic variance, incorrect for non-isotropic diagonal Σ)

train.py, train_publication.py, evaluation.py, evaluate_test_set.py:
- Cap all exp(loss) perplexity computations to prevent float overflow

analysis/rg_flow_enhanced.py:
- Fix dimension bug: skip mean(dim=0) when kl_matrix is already 2D

analysis/semantics.py:
- Replace float('inf') with large finite value when mean_intra ≈ 0

visualization/belief_space_frequent.py:
- Fix sys.path: go up 3 levels to project root (was only 1 level)
- Add missing torch import

tests/transformer/test_ffn.py:
- Add GaugeFFN test coverage: creation, forward pass, beta history,
  error handling, numerical stability, factory function, multi-iteration

